name: Essential pentosuria
ghr-page: https://ghr.nlm.nih.gov/condition/essential-pentosuria
text/text-role: description
text/html/html:p: Essential pentosuria is a condition characterized by high levels of a sugar called L-xylulose in urine. The condition is so named because L-xylulose is a type of sugar called a pentose. Despite the excess sugar, affected individuals have no associated health problems.
inheritance-pattern/code: ar
inheritance-pattern/memo: autosomal recessive
related-gene/gene-symbol: DCXR
related-gene/ghr-page: https://ghr.nlm.nih.gov/gene/DCXR
synonym(1): essential benign pentosuria
synonym(2): L-xylulose reductase deficiency
synonym(3): L-xylulosuria
synonym(4): pentosuria
synonym(5): xylitol dehydrogenase deficiency
